1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:06,089
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:13,847
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:16,641 --> 00:00:19,436
I know a gig. One thousand per night.

4
00:00:19,519 --> 00:00:21,563
[Ame] <i>Why do they pay that much?</i>

5
00:00:21,646 --> 00:00:23,148
[Bebang] <i>Come with me. I’ll show you.</i>

6
00:00:23,231 --> 00:00:24,274
[Ibyang] Ame?

7
00:00:24,357 --> 00:00:25,442
Ame!

8
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:27,318
Ame!

9
00:00:27,402 --> 00:00:29,487
Hey, kid. What’s up? What happened to you?

10
00:00:29,571 --> 00:00:32,073
My sister Ame is missing.

11
00:00:32,157 --> 00:00:36,745
I know someone who’s really good
at finding missing people.

12
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:38,246
You?

13
00:00:38,329 --> 00:00:39,497
[Ibyang] <i>You’re so grumpy!</i>

14
00:00:39,581 --> 00:00:40,957
What’s that?

15
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:42,542
An old bachelor?

16
00:00:43,376 --> 00:00:44,919
I know, he’s really grumpy.

17
00:00:45,503 --> 00:00:47,130
I don’t like stubborn people.

18
00:00:47,213 --> 00:00:49,632
[chiming]

19
00:00:49,716 --> 00:00:51,217
Is that a ghost, Brother Atoy?

20
00:00:51,301 --> 00:00:52,927
PREVIOUSLY

21
00:00:53,011 --> 00:00:54,054
[Ibyang] <i>You teleported!</i>

22
00:00:54,137 --> 00:00:55,847
<i>It’s like you’re a magician or something!</i>

23
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:57,348
[Atoy] <i>Give me what you took.</i>
<i>Hand it over now.</i>

24
00:00:57,432 --> 00:00:58,266
<i>It’s important to me.</i>

25
00:00:58,349 --> 00:01:00,852
Brother Atoy, watch out!

26
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:02,187
[clanks]

27
00:01:02,270 --> 00:01:03,730
[Ibyang] <i>Don’t be grumpy with me.</i>

28
00:01:03,813 --> 00:01:05,065
<i>I saved you.</i>

29
00:01:05,148 --> 00:01:07,025
[Cita] <i>The child is so helpless and alone.</i>

30
00:01:07,108 --> 00:01:10,070
<i>She’s so small. You should</i>
<i>have just brought her here.</i>

31
00:01:10,153 --> 00:01:11,905
[Atoy] <i>You should stay at home!</i>

32
00:01:11,988 --> 00:01:14,491
I live in that old bus.

33
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:16,868
[Ibyang] <i>My big sister Ame</i>
<i>and I are homeless.</i>

34
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:19,788
[Atoy] <i>We’ll look for your sister, okay?</i>

35
00:01:25,627 --> 00:01:28,963
[clattering in distance]

36
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:45,396
[cheeky music playing]

37
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:49,192
[Ibyang] Pork tocino is ready.

38
00:01:49,275 --> 00:01:51,778
Good morning, Master Sung…

39
00:01:51,861 --> 00:01:53,613
Master Handsome!

40
00:01:53,696 --> 00:01:55,824
[in English] Breakfast is almost ready!

41
00:01:55,907 --> 00:01:58,785
The rice is almost cooked too.

42
00:01:59,577 --> 00:02:02,539
- Huh? What’s this?
- [whimsical flourish]

43
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:04,207
- Tocino!
- What kind of tocino is that?

44
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:05,416
It looks totally burnt.

45
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:08,461
Looks like it was cremated. Looks like…

46
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:09,879
Is that charcoal?

47
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:11,297
[chuckles]

48
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:13,007
I miscalculated.

49
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:15,635
It’s my first time
in a kitchen with a stove.

50
00:02:15,718 --> 00:02:18,888
- [Atoy] Ah…
- The others aren’t too burnt.

51
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:20,014
Here, eat the eggs.

52
00:02:20,098 --> 00:02:22,517
That’s not burnt. Just a little.

53
00:02:23,351 --> 00:02:28,398
Thanks anyway.
I just drink coffee in the morning.

54
00:02:28,481 --> 00:02:31,067
Well, I just made it.

55
00:02:31,693 --> 00:02:35,071
I also bought
from Mang Pandesal, but I said…

56
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:37,699
you’ll pay.

57
00:02:37,782 --> 00:02:41,995
[cheeky music continues]

58
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:49,002
- Master Handsome.
- Why are you so pesky?

59
00:02:49,085 --> 00:02:51,337
I thought you were sick, huh?

60
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:52,839
You’re so chatty.

61
00:02:52,922 --> 00:02:55,091
Thanks again.

62
00:02:55,174 --> 00:02:59,512
Thank you for coming to get me
and letting me sleep here.

63
00:03:02,515 --> 00:03:06,269
[gentle music playing]

64
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:09,856
Go on, eat now. Go on.

65
00:03:10,607 --> 00:03:11,900
- Here, sit!
- [Atoy mutters]

66
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:14,193
- Go on.
- We’ll pray now!

67
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:16,070
- Hurry.
- All right.

68
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:24,203
[in English] In the name of the Father,
Son, Holy Spirit. Amen.

69
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:28,917
[in English] Bless us, O Lord,
and these thy gifts,

70
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,169
which we are about to receive.

71
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:32,962
[in English] Amen.

72
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:36,382
[in English] In the name of the Father,
and the Son, and the Holy Spirit. Amen.

73
00:03:40,386 --> 00:03:41,888
You know how to pray.

74
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:44,224
Of course!

75
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:46,309
My big sister Ame taught me.

76
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:47,518
[spits]

77
00:03:47,602 --> 00:03:51,856
So, when will you start…

78
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:53,900
looking for Ame?

79
00:03:55,777 --> 00:03:56,778
[inhales]

80
00:03:56,861 --> 00:03:57,904
Eh…

81
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:03,284
When was the last time
you saw your sister?

82
00:04:03,993 --> 00:04:05,119
Where was the last place
you were together?

83
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:11,542
The day we met you.

84
00:04:11,626 --> 00:04:12,710
Have you heard?

85
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:14,587
The village officer came earlier.

86
00:04:15,171 --> 00:04:16,839
- This land has been sold,
- [unsettling music]

87
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:19,717
and we need to leave
before the month ends.

88
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:22,679
Huh? It’s so sudden.

89
00:04:23,388 --> 00:04:24,514
Yes, I know.

90
00:04:24,597 --> 00:04:26,766
But what can we do?

91
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:28,685
We’re all squatters here.

92
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:31,854
- What will happen to us, Ame?
- I’ll find a way.

93
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:33,690
Ah, this is what I’ll do…

94
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:36,609
I’ll go to Mister John’s shop.

95
00:04:36,693 --> 00:04:38,611
Maybe it’s still open.

96
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:40,280
I’ll sell the cellphone too.

97
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:41,698
I’ll go with you.

98
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:46,619
No. Stay here. Go to sleep.

99
00:04:47,495 --> 00:04:49,872
Or you’ll end up like me, never grew tall.

100
00:04:51,332 --> 00:04:52,667
- Huh?
- [chuckles]

101
00:04:55,044 --> 00:04:55,878
Bye.

102
00:04:56,796 --> 00:05:03,594
I thought we’d meet at our spot,
but she didn’t come.

103
00:05:03,678 --> 00:05:06,723
Did you talk to that Mister John?

104
00:05:06,806 --> 00:05:09,892
Did you ask him if he knew anything?

105
00:05:10,601 --> 00:05:16,024
I went back to his place many times,
but it was always closed.

106
00:05:16,816 --> 00:05:19,068
- Fine, fine, fine.
- [brazen music playing]

107
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:21,154
I’ll go see Mister John.

108
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:23,072
What’s his address again?

109
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:25,825
Wait… You’re not taking me?

110
00:05:25,908 --> 00:05:28,328
No. Stay here. You’ll just stay here.

111
00:05:28,911 --> 00:05:35,710
Eh… I don’t know the address,
but I know how to get there.

112
00:05:36,669 --> 00:05:40,923
If you don’t take me, nothing will happen.

113
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:42,925
- [cheeky music playing]
- [mutters]

114
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:46,012
Fine, fine, fine, I’ll take you.
I’ll take you.

115
00:05:46,637 --> 00:05:47,972
[in English] Yes!

116
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:49,432
You’ll really help me?

117
00:05:49,515 --> 00:05:50,516
Yes.

118
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:53,978
I hope I can do this
before my eardrums break and--

119
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:54,896
What’s that?

120
00:05:54,979 --> 00:05:56,606
[pot whistling]

121
00:05:56,689 --> 00:05:57,940
The rice!

122
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:01,861
Cremated too.

123
00:06:01,944 --> 00:06:06,657
[suave music playing]

124
00:06:08,367 --> 00:06:12,663
[engine roaring]

125
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:14,582
[scraping]

126
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:19,504
[sewing machine whirring]

127
00:06:19,587 --> 00:06:21,839
- [gun cocks]
- [gunshots blasting]

128
00:06:21,923 --> 00:06:22,882
[gunshots blasting]

129
00:06:22,965 --> 00:06:25,176
[whirring]

130
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:26,594
[snipping]

131
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:37,772
- Atoy! Brother!
- [Atoy] Oh?

132
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:39,607
- Mom sent something.
- [Atoy] Oh.

133
00:06:39,690 --> 00:06:41,651
Clothes for Ibyang. Who’s that?

134
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:43,236
- It’s me!
- [whimsical music]

135
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:45,655
Hey, what are you doing here, you imp?

136
00:06:45,738 --> 00:06:47,240
Come here!

137
00:06:47,907 --> 00:06:49,450
I live here.

138
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:50,827
Master, tell her.

139
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:51,953
[cheeky music playing]

140
00:06:52,036 --> 00:06:54,038
Atoy, are you letting her stay here?

141
00:06:54,122 --> 00:06:55,081
Did she hypnotize you?

142
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:59,085
She asked me to help her find her sister.

143
00:06:59,168 --> 00:07:00,461
We were about to leave.

144
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:02,880
But you’re here now.

145
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:06,843
- Oh, no! She’s a snatcher!
- Hey, I didn’t do anything to you.

146
00:07:06,926 --> 00:07:07,760
[funky music playing]

147
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:13,433
You should’ve brought coins,
so you wouldn’t need a QR code.

148
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:16,185
So it’s my fault you stole my cellphone?

149
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:19,105
Psst. Hey, enough, enough, enough.

150
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:22,859
You kept using your cellphone.

151
00:07:22,942 --> 00:07:24,610
So, now it’s gone.

152
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:25,945
Serves you right.

153
00:07:26,028 --> 00:07:28,364
You’re still so young,
yet already a scammer.

154
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:31,200
And you, you’re so old,
and still you got scammed.

155
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:32,910
Where’s my cellphone?

156
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:35,663
Ask the turtle.

157
00:07:35,746 --> 00:07:37,039
Hey, hey, hey. Here.

158
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:38,040
Take the scissors.

159
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:40,626
Maybe you want to kill each other
if you’re not gonna stop.

160
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:43,588
Hurry, so I can leave.

161
00:07:45,089 --> 00:07:46,674
Well?

162
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:49,469
Are you okay now?

163
00:07:51,596 --> 00:07:56,684
Karla, help Liit get dressed
in the comfort room.

164
00:07:57,894 --> 00:07:59,979
- Go on.
- [Ibyang] I’ll do it!

165
00:08:00,062 --> 00:08:04,150
She might choke me if we’re alone there.

166
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:05,902
Atoy, when she comes out of the CR,

167
00:08:05,985 --> 00:08:08,070
check your newly bought soap.

168
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:10,323
If she’s a snatcher,
she’ll strike anywhere.

169
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:13,242
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Go on. Here.

170
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:16,454
[Karla] Get dressed.

171
00:08:17,455 --> 00:08:19,582
- Oh, you don’t want to?
- Hmm.

172
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:21,751
[Ibyang] She’s taller than me,

173
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:24,921
but I can take on Karla.

174
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:27,381
Hey, it's big sister Karla.

175
00:08:27,465 --> 00:08:28,549
She’s still older than you.

176
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,676
You need to learn respect.

177
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:32,345
Mmm, don’t worry.

178
00:08:32,428 --> 00:08:33,346
I know you’ll get along.

179
00:08:33,429 --> 00:08:34,347
You’re both mischievous.

180
00:08:35,681 --> 00:08:37,517
Who are we supposed to talk to?

181
00:08:38,434 --> 00:08:39,352
Him?

182
00:08:40,269 --> 00:08:41,521
[Ibyang] That’s Mister John!

183
00:08:41,604 --> 00:08:43,231
[ominous music playing]

184
00:08:43,314 --> 00:08:45,066
- Uh, may I ask a question--
- Mister John, why are you just--

185
00:08:45,733 --> 00:08:47,318
Let me, let me.

186
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:49,403
They don’t know you.

187
00:08:50,154 --> 00:08:51,489
- Mister Jo--
- Um…

188
00:08:51,572 --> 00:08:54,408
I’m Atoy.

189
00:08:54,492 --> 00:08:56,994
I just want to ask you something.

190
00:08:58,037 --> 00:09:00,164
This child has been
looking for you for days.

191
00:09:00,248 --> 00:09:04,460
She said you were one
of the last people to talk to Ame.

192
00:09:05,086 --> 00:09:06,629
Do you know where she is?

193
00:09:06,712 --> 00:09:09,131
She came here the other day.

194
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:10,299
She wanted to borrow money.

195
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:12,760
But I had nothing to lend her.

196
00:09:12,843 --> 00:09:15,471
So, I referred her to Bebang.

197
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:17,473
[both] Who’s Bebang?

198
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:20,518
[in English] The "talent manager".

199
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:23,187
They were the last ones
to talk about the side job,

200
00:09:23,271 --> 00:09:25,147
but I don’t know if it pushed through.

201
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:26,607
What side job?

202
00:09:27,358 --> 00:09:28,442
I don’t know.

203
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:29,569
‪[sinister music playing]

204
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:35,157
Do you know where I can find her?

205
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:37,243
Or where she lives?
Or where I can talk to her?

206
00:09:43,624 --> 00:09:44,917
Next time, Master,

207
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:46,752
don’t cover my mouth.

208
00:09:47,461 --> 00:09:49,797
- Or else I’ll definitely bite you.
- [shushes]

209
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:53,384
Zip. Zip it.

210
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:55,177
[curious music playing]

211
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:56,220
Shut up.

212
00:09:56,971 --> 00:09:58,472
I don’t want to hear…

213
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:00,766
Anybody home?

214
00:10:03,477 --> 00:10:04,562
Hello!

215
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:09,942
[curious music continues]

216
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:10,901
Hello.

217
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:16,115
Anybody home?

218
00:10:18,701 --> 00:10:20,119
Ma’am Bebang!

219
00:10:20,202 --> 00:10:21,329
Miss Bebang!

220
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:22,872
[in English] Madam Bebang!

221
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:24,373
Yoo-hoo!

222
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:25,958
- Are you here?
- [dog barking]

223
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:28,586
- [curious music playing]
- [scoffs]

224
00:10:28,669 --> 00:10:30,254
I told you to shut up.

225
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:33,382
[soft groans]

226
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:45,853
Whoa… What’s that?

227
00:10:45,936 --> 00:10:47,355
- What’s this?
- Hmm.

228
00:10:47,438 --> 00:10:48,856
[in English] Special toy.

229
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:59,116
[ominous music playing]

230
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:03,162
[clicking]

231
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:09,627
‪[metal screeching]

232
00:11:12,797 --> 00:11:14,256
[gate screeches open]

233
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:19,178
Cool?

234
00:11:23,974 --> 00:11:25,518
[clicking]

235
00:11:33,025 --> 00:11:34,026
[rattling]

236
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:44,370
[door creaks]

237
00:11:45,413 --> 00:11:46,914
[funky music playing]

238
00:11:46,997 --> 00:11:47,998
Hey…

239
00:11:50,209 --> 00:11:51,127
How…?

240
00:11:51,961 --> 00:11:52,920
What…?

241
00:11:54,255 --> 00:11:55,589
There.

242
00:11:56,674 --> 00:11:59,468
You’ve got all those special tools,

243
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:01,595
but I’m all you need.

244
00:12:02,304 --> 00:12:05,349
And yet you didn’t
want to take me with you.

245
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:08,310
Get in.

246
00:12:09,937 --> 00:12:13,983
[upbeat music playing]

247
00:12:29,498 --> 00:12:33,085
[ominous music playing]

248
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:35,379
What are we looking for?

249
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:37,590
Psst! Hey!

250
00:12:37,673 --> 00:12:39,758
Don’t-- Don’t eat that.

251
00:12:39,842 --> 00:12:40,801
Throw it away.

252
00:12:42,636 --> 00:12:43,512
Throw it.

253
00:12:49,768 --> 00:12:51,020
Is this it?

254
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:52,605
This is her picture.

255
00:12:52,688 --> 00:12:54,106
That’s who we’re looking for.

256
00:12:59,737 --> 00:13:01,989
How do you know it’s her?

257
00:13:02,072 --> 00:13:03,365
There are so many of them.

258
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:07,369
Well, look for the common denominator
in the pictures.

259
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:10,331
[in English] Common denomi…

260
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:11,957
What’s that?

261
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,502
You should study.

262
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:16,003
[camera shutter snapping]

263
00:13:16,086 --> 00:13:17,505
Like this.

264
00:13:17,588 --> 00:13:19,924
Look at all these, that face.

265
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:27,473
[upbeat music playing]

266
00:13:29,934 --> 00:13:32,728
Wow… Why are you scavenging now?

267
00:13:35,022 --> 00:13:36,023
Be quiet.

268
00:13:44,823 --> 00:13:46,033
This is recent.

269
00:13:49,453 --> 00:13:50,788
We have somewhere to go.

270
00:13:51,705 --> 00:13:52,998
I don’t like pesky people, okay?

271
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:55,751
I’ll take you, but don’t be annoying.

272
00:13:56,794 --> 00:13:57,836
Mmm, okay.

273
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:00,047
‪[music intensifies, concludes]

274
00:14:04,635 --> 00:14:06,637
- Boss…
- Boss…

275
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:09,557
What’s up, boss?

276
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,100
Boss, do you see her around?

277
00:14:12,268 --> 00:14:14,353
Yes, boss, I see her every morning.

278
00:14:14,436 --> 00:14:16,105
I see her coming from there.

279
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:20,484
Really?

280
00:14:21,151 --> 00:14:23,445
- Why are you looking for her?
- Why?

281
00:14:25,155 --> 00:14:28,117
Well… you know, Bebang…

282
00:14:29,785 --> 00:14:31,203
She has been ignoring me.

283
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:33,163
No matter how many messages I send,

284
00:14:33,247 --> 00:14:36,917
no matter how many calls, she doesn’t…

285
00:14:37,001 --> 00:14:39,628
Maybe she’s mad at me.

286
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:42,840
Well, come back tomorrow morning, sir.

287
00:14:44,508 --> 00:14:47,219
Perhaps she’ll be there.
I’ll go right now.

288
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:48,596
That place opens at night, sir,

289
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:50,639
and the entrance fee is steep.

290
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:51,807
You might poke a hole in your wallet.

291
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:54,768
But I heard the ladies there
are first-class.

292
00:14:57,813 --> 00:15:00,190
There are chicks inside that place?

293
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:03,903
Aren’t they supposed to be in farms?

294
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:07,615
Chicks, sexy girls, not chickens.

295
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:08,824
Psst, hey!

296
00:15:09,366 --> 00:15:10,200
SPG, bro.

297
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:12,912
You’re talking to a kid,
not your drinking buddy.

298
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:13,871
Oh, sorry.

299
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:21,837
Why would Miss Bebang take my sister
inside a place with sexy girls?

300
00:15:22,504 --> 00:15:24,673
My sister Ame isn’t sexy,

301
00:15:24,757 --> 00:15:25,841
and she’s short.

302
00:15:27,927 --> 00:15:30,471
Looks like there’s some
shady business happening inside.

303
00:15:33,223 --> 00:15:34,600
Come on. Let’s go home.

304
00:15:34,683 --> 00:15:36,268
Let’s eat first!

305
00:15:36,352 --> 00:15:38,938
We haven’t even ordered here.

306
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:40,606
I love siomai.

307
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:42,942
Eat at home instead. Come on!

308
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:45,694
But it’s far from here!

309
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:46,946
Come on.

310
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:49,239
[in English] Please, Master.

311
00:15:49,323 --> 00:15:52,117
I’m really hungry.

312
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:56,747
[Ibyang] The food here
looks delicious, Master.

313
00:15:57,790 --> 00:15:59,124
- What do you think?
- Mmm.

314
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:01,251
What do you want?

315
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:03,712
Tapsilog is the best here.

316
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:05,839
- Or chicksilog, you want?
- [Ibyang] Tapsilog?

317
00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:07,841
- Mmm…
- Hotsilog?

318
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:08,759
Okay, hotsilog.

319
00:16:10,344 --> 00:16:11,553
[Ibyang mutters]

320
00:16:11,637 --> 00:16:13,097
[woman] Wow, I’m full.

321
00:16:13,180 --> 00:16:14,807
[Ibyang] Let’s check first.

322
00:16:14,890 --> 00:16:17,309
Oh, miss.

323
00:16:17,393 --> 00:16:19,228
Hey, I heard you speaking Bisaya earlier?

324
00:16:19,311 --> 00:16:20,854
- I’m from Carcar.
- [indistinct chattering]

325
00:16:20,938 --> 00:16:22,189
- Did you just arrive in Manila?
- [woman mumbles]

326
00:16:22,773 --> 00:16:26,485
Yes, it’s my first time riding a plane,

327
00:16:26,568 --> 00:16:28,487
and the taxi was expensive.

328
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:30,406
- They even dropped me off
- [mutters]

329
00:16:30,489 --> 00:16:32,866
at the wrong place earlier.

330
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:34,827
Oh, wait, how much is mine?

331
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:38,831
One pares and vegetables,

332
00:16:38,914 --> 00:16:42,418
rice, leche flan, and water.

333
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:46,171
Okay. 220 pesos in total.

334
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:48,465
I’ll give you the water
and leche flan for free

335
00:16:48,549 --> 00:16:51,802
- as a welcome gift to Manila.
- [chuckles] That's great!

336
00:16:51,885 --> 00:16:52,720
[male customer 1] Miss!

337
00:16:54,096 --> 00:16:55,264
Are you new in Manila?

338
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:57,641
You can live with me.

339
00:16:57,725 --> 00:16:59,018
Why would I live with you?

340
00:16:59,101 --> 00:17:00,144
I don’t even know you.

341
00:17:00,227 --> 00:17:02,146
Maybe you’re looking for a master.

342
00:17:02,229 --> 00:17:03,480
You look like you’re good…

343
00:17:03,564 --> 00:17:05,482
- in bed.
- [male customer 1 laughing]

344
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:07,192
Cleaning the bed, I mean!

345
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:08,944
- There! Make it clear!
- [both laugh]

346
00:17:10,404 --> 00:17:12,072
[speaking in Bisaya] Hey, you two pests!

347
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:13,323
Just because I'm Bisaya,

348
00:17:13,407 --> 00:17:16,285
it doesn't mean I'm a maid!
You two maybe from Manila,

349
00:17:16,368 --> 00:17:18,203
but do you even know anything
about Subject-Verb Agreement?

350
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:20,205
I am sure you don't!
And by the way you two look,

351
00:17:20,289 --> 00:17:22,416
you look like you're unemployed! Damn you!

352
00:17:23,917 --> 00:17:24,918
[men chuckle]

353
00:17:25,836 --> 00:17:27,171
What now, bro?

354
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:29,256
I like feisty Bisaya girls.

355
00:17:29,339 --> 00:17:32,092
Just total it and then I’ll handle…

356
00:17:32,176 --> 00:17:34,053
- [male customer 1] Don’t be mad.
- [scoffs]

357
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:36,096
[male customer 1] Come on!

358
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:37,347
[male customer 1] Come with me.
Don’t resist--

359
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:38,932
- [male customer 1] You’re acting coy.
- What?

360
00:17:39,016 --> 00:17:39,850
[male customer 1] Come on!

361
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:41,143
- [shrieks]
- [man grunts]

362
00:17:42,811 --> 00:17:44,772
- Come on, come on!
- [woman breathing panicky]

363
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:47,274
Bro, don’t fight back.

364
00:17:47,357 --> 00:17:49,109
So? Does it feel good to be slapped?

365
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:50,486
[grunting]

366
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:51,403
‪[grunting and groaning]

367
00:17:51,779 --> 00:17:52,905
[thudding]

368
00:17:56,492 --> 00:17:58,869
- Beat him up, quick!
- Huh? Huh?

369
00:17:58,952 --> 00:18:00,954
- Hit him. Go on.
- [stammering]

370
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:02,164
- [grunts]
- [groans]

371
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:05,626
Brother! That’s what you get!

372
00:18:05,709 --> 00:18:07,544
- You’re so arrogant!
- Shh, it’s okay, it’s okay.

373
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:10,380
- [shrieks]
- [suave music playing]

374
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:13,425
- [grunts]
- [woman shrieks]

375
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:16,136
[woman] Wow…

376
00:18:19,932 --> 00:18:22,309
Oh, be wary of those troublemakers, okay?

377
00:18:22,392 --> 00:18:24,394
- Ah, that was intense.
- [playful sensual music]

378
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:26,480
Thank you for saving me.

379
00:18:26,563 --> 00:18:28,899
Ah, thank you, Keye.

380
00:18:29,483 --> 00:18:30,818
- [giggles]
- Huh?

381
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:32,111
Wha…t? What’s Keye?

382
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:34,279
[Ibyang] That’s big brother, Master.

383
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:36,115
She’s just being cute.

384
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:38,534
Be careful.

385
00:18:39,076 --> 00:18:40,828
[funky music playing]

386
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:43,163
Let’s go. I lost my appetite.

387
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:46,250
[shrieks, chuckles]

388
00:18:46,333 --> 00:18:49,461
Lord, is he the one on my checklist, Lord?

389
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:52,631
Wow, you really checked all the boxes.

390
00:18:52,714 --> 00:18:54,299
[in English] Tall? Check!

391
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:56,343
Mestizo? [in English] Oh, check!

392
00:18:56,426 --> 00:18:58,303
[in English] Handsome? Ah, double check!

393
00:18:59,179 --> 00:19:00,013
This is it.

394
00:19:00,097 --> 00:19:04,143
He’s really the perfect example of TDH.

395
00:19:06,019 --> 00:19:08,772
Thank you. Please fix it, okay?

396
00:19:08,856 --> 00:19:10,899
[indistinct chattering]

397
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:12,818
[Paldo] Morning, bro! Where are we going?

398
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:17,906
[Paldo] Yes, I’ll handle it,
I’ll handle it.

399
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,825
[Paldo] What do you want to drink?

400
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:22,619
[man] Beer then, beer.

401
00:19:22,703 --> 00:19:26,999
- [uplifting music playing]
- [indistinct chatter]

402
00:19:27,082 --> 00:19:29,126
[man] I’ll take care of the lechon.

403
00:19:30,961 --> 00:19:33,255
[Paldo] I’ll take care of you.

404
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:54,568
[crowd buzzing]

405
00:19:54,651 --> 00:19:55,485
[man] Hey!

406
00:19:55,569 --> 00:19:57,696
Uh, Miss, hi.

407
00:19:57,779 --> 00:20:01,909
Um… I’m the village captain here.

408
00:20:01,992 --> 00:20:04,244
Are you looking for someone here, or…

409
00:20:05,746 --> 00:20:06,997
[in English] Is it me you’re looking for?

410
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:08,916
[chic music playing]

411
00:20:08,999 --> 00:20:09,958
[clears throat]

412
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:11,001
[in English] Sorry.

413
00:20:11,084 --> 00:20:13,295
I already found my TDH.

414
00:20:13,378 --> 00:20:14,504
- Ah, really?
- [woman] Yes.

415
00:20:14,588 --> 00:20:16,131
- Can I catch up?
- [woman] No.

416
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:18,425
[indistinct chatter]

417
00:20:23,263 --> 00:20:24,806
[Bunda] Jesus Mary Joseph!
There's a fiesta going on!

418
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:27,601
- Ah, hello, Auntie!
- Beautiful!

419
00:20:27,684 --> 00:20:28,644
Oh, what?

420
00:20:28,727 --> 00:20:30,646
- Um, can I ask a question?
- [Bunda] What?

421
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:32,814
Is there a rental place
here in Tabang Lupa?

422
00:20:32,898 --> 00:20:34,691
- We know one, right?
- [in English] Yes.

423
00:20:34,775 --> 00:20:36,276
We know someone.

424
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:38,362
She has a boarding house here,
just nearby.

425
00:20:38,445 --> 00:20:44,368
But she’s at the tailoring shop
right now, right?

426
00:20:44,451 --> 00:20:46,495
- [women muttering]
- Ah, tailoring shop? Whose?

427
00:20:46,578 --> 00:20:47,412
- [Bunda] Huh?
- Whose?

428
00:20:47,496 --> 00:20:49,331
- Oh, she doesn’t know.
- [chuckles]

429
00:20:49,414 --> 00:20:52,000
- Mister Delfin’s. Here’s what you do.
- [woman 2] Hmm.

430
00:20:52,084 --> 00:20:53,543
Go straight there.

431
00:20:53,627 --> 00:20:56,380
When you get to the corner,
turn right, okay?

432
00:20:56,463 --> 00:20:57,506
When you turn right,

433
00:20:57,589 --> 00:21:01,260
you’ll see "Mang Delfin’s
Tailoring Shop", okay?

434
00:21:01,343 --> 00:21:04,137
Then look for Miss Cita there.

435
00:21:04,221 --> 00:21:07,391
- Okay? Cita Samonte, okay?
- [woman 1 mumbles]

436
00:21:07,474 --> 00:21:08,767
There. Mmm. Ah…

437
00:21:08,850 --> 00:21:10,852
Uh, by the way. I'm Bunda.

438
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:12,145
- Uh… Tonet.
- [chuckles]

439
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:13,272
- Tonet.
- Yes, Tonet.

440
00:21:13,355 --> 00:21:14,940
- Bobby, Bobby.
- Tonet.

441
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:15,941
- There.
- Oh, Tonet.

442
00:21:16,024 --> 00:21:16,858
Joana!

443
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:18,777
- Mona. Jona!
- [giggles]

444
00:21:18,860 --> 00:21:20,737
- [Bunda] They sound alike. Tonet!
- [women laugh]

445
00:21:20,821 --> 00:21:22,572
- You’re so cute, Tonet.
- [woman 3] Tonet…

446
00:21:22,656 --> 00:21:24,074
- [woman 2] Be careful, huh?
- [Bunda] Take care!

447
00:21:24,157 --> 00:21:25,200
Are you about to do Zumba?

448
00:21:25,284 --> 00:21:26,285
- [Tonet] Bye-bye.
- [Bunda mumbles]

449
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:29,288
[indistinct chatter]

450
00:21:29,371 --> 00:21:30,330
[Bunda] Take care.

451
00:21:31,832 --> 00:21:33,583
[Karla] All right, Mom, I’ll go now.

452
00:21:33,667 --> 00:21:36,128
Hold it properly.

453
00:21:36,211 --> 00:21:38,046
[Cita] Wait, fix it.

454
00:21:38,630 --> 00:21:41,049
- I’m not an assistant here.
- [scissors snipping]

455
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:43,302
I don’t want to rot in the shop like you.

456
00:21:43,385 --> 00:21:45,053
- What did you say?
- [whimsical music]

457
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:46,513
Nothing.

458
00:21:49,057 --> 00:21:50,309
[snipping]

459
00:21:50,392 --> 00:21:51,601
[chiming]

460
00:21:51,685 --> 00:21:52,519
[Cita gasps]

461
00:21:52,602 --> 00:21:54,604
[Tonet, in English] Hello, everybody!

462
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:56,481
Uh, are you Manang Cita?

463
00:21:56,565 --> 00:21:58,275
- Yes, that’s me. What do you need?
- [Tonet] Ah…

464
00:21:58,358 --> 00:22:01,945
Bunda mentioned that you have
a rental place here.

465
00:22:02,029 --> 00:22:05,657
Ah… Yes, I have one just for you.

466
00:22:05,741 --> 00:22:07,034
Three thousand per month.

467
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:08,702
One month advance.

468
00:22:08,785 --> 00:22:11,204
And you’re not picky, right?

469
00:22:11,288 --> 00:22:13,457
We only have an electric fan, no aircon.

470
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:15,167
Ah, electric fan is fine.

471
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:16,251
I’m not used to aircon.

472
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:18,670
- I’m used to natural air.
- [whimsical music]

473
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:21,340
Oh, natural pollution
is what we have here.

474
00:22:21,423 --> 00:22:24,468
And sometimes, Mickey Mouse
peeks through the holes.

475
00:22:24,551 --> 00:22:25,552
Karla!

476
00:22:25,635 --> 00:22:28,055
[Tonet] Okay…

477
00:22:28,764 --> 00:22:29,723
Oh!

478
00:22:30,515 --> 00:22:31,683
- [Tonet] Hup!
- [Karla] Hey!

479
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,935
Don’t touch that. That’s Brother Atoy’s.

480
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:35,812
Oh, sorry, I just got OC.

481
00:22:35,896 --> 00:22:38,982
Brother Atoy doesn’t like
his things touched.

482
00:22:39,524 --> 00:22:44,738
If you do, he’ll cut your whole being
until you’re just scraps.

483
00:22:44,821 --> 00:22:46,656
Karla, you’re exaggerating.

484
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:50,368
He’s kind, just a bit grumpy,
but he’s okay.

485
00:22:50,452 --> 00:22:51,995
Where is that Atoy?

486
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:53,789
He’s got me intrigued.

487
00:22:53,872 --> 00:22:56,958
Maybe he’ll fall for my natural charm.

488
00:22:57,584 --> 00:23:01,296
[funky music playing]

489
00:23:01,922 --> 00:23:05,967
[Ibyang] Master, that woman you saved
seems compatible with you.

490
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:07,594
Do you like her?

491
00:23:08,178 --> 00:23:09,054
No.

492
00:23:09,596 --> 00:23:13,725
Maybe you’ve saved
a lot of women before, huh?

493
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:17,687
- You’re really good at fighting!
- [gentle music playing]

494
00:23:18,355 --> 00:23:19,606
Where did you learn that?

495
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:23,068
You know, you should
just finish your food.

496
00:23:23,151 --> 00:23:24,027
Hurry up, so you can go home.

497
00:23:24,111 --> 00:23:25,862
I still need to go back to Endless Nights.

498
00:23:25,946 --> 00:23:28,990
Just take me with you tonight, Master,

499
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:30,283
when you go back there.

500
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:32,202
Kids aren’t allowed there.

501
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:36,456
What you should do is go home.

502
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:42,420
You should eat, bathe,
sleep, clean… Those things.

503
00:23:42,504 --> 00:23:44,381
So, you’ll grow taller, sleep.

504
00:23:44,464 --> 00:23:46,424
I’m already tall.

505
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:52,097
Someday, you’ll need me in your missions.

506
00:23:52,180 --> 00:23:54,474
I’ve been doing this alone
for a long time.

507
00:23:55,142 --> 00:23:57,352
I don’t need anyone to help me.

508
00:23:57,894 --> 00:24:01,064
You’ll eat those words,

509
00:24:01,940 --> 00:24:03,942
and you’ll choke on them.

510
00:24:04,025 --> 00:24:04,860
- [coughs]
- [whimsical music playing]

511
00:24:04,943 --> 00:24:09,906
No one will bring you water except me.

512
00:24:10,740 --> 00:24:13,493
Ah, is that so? My wife, oh.

513
00:24:14,452 --> 00:24:15,662
[chuckles]

514
00:24:15,745 --> 00:24:17,539
But you don’t have a girlfriend.

515
00:24:17,622 --> 00:24:19,583
[chuckles]

516
00:24:19,666 --> 00:24:21,376
Why is that?

517
00:24:22,002 --> 00:24:23,712
You’re handsome.

518
00:24:24,754 --> 00:24:27,007
Do you have a problem here?

519
00:24:27,716 --> 00:24:29,718
Or do you have smelly feet?

520
00:24:30,468 --> 00:24:32,053
Ah, smelly feet, huh?

521
00:24:32,137 --> 00:24:33,597
Go on, insult me more.

522
00:24:34,222 --> 00:24:37,726
So, kid? Do you still
want to see your sister? Well?

523
00:24:37,809 --> 00:24:41,021
- [Atoy] Hmm?
- I was just joking.

524
00:24:41,104 --> 00:24:43,815
- [in English] Erase, erase, erase.
- It’s better we’re clear.

525
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:47,694
Your girlfriend will be lucky

526
00:24:48,612 --> 00:24:52,699
because you’ll always protect
and think of her.

527
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:53,658
Mmm.

528
00:24:57,287 --> 00:24:59,164
[gentle music playing]

529
00:25:00,707 --> 00:25:01,541
‪[suave music playing]

530
00:25:02,417 --> 00:25:03,293
Godmother!

531
00:25:04,419 --> 00:25:07,714
[suave music continues]

532
00:25:11,301 --> 00:25:12,677
- [gasps, screams]
- [whimsical boinking]

533
00:25:12,761 --> 00:25:14,012
Pervert!

534
00:25:16,723 --> 00:25:17,724
The scissors!

535
00:25:22,562 --> 00:25:25,815
[dreamy music playing]

536
00:25:25,899 --> 00:25:27,651
TDH…

537
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:35,325
[electronic blipping]

538
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:43,375
- Don’t you know me?
- I don’t talk to drivers.

539
00:25:43,458 --> 00:25:45,460
Idiot, I’m the boss! [groans]

540
00:25:45,543 --> 00:25:47,045
I want to leave.

541
00:25:47,128 --> 00:25:49,297
[Ame] <i>I don’t know how to do this!</i>

542
00:25:49,381 --> 00:25:51,800
So that’s how cruel
it is inside there, huh?

543
00:25:51,883 --> 00:25:54,469
[in English] It’s exclusive membership,
not open to the public.

544
00:25:54,552 --> 00:25:55,804
Why would he hang out
in a place like this?

545
00:25:55,887 --> 00:25:57,722
Do you think he knows
what I did to his father,

546
00:25:57,806 --> 00:25:59,641
- that’s why he showed up here?
- [thug] Psst.

547
00:25:59,724 --> 00:26:01,393
- Now, show me how tough you are.
- [Atoy] Ah…

548
00:26:01,476 --> 00:26:02,310
NEXT

549
00:26:02,394 --> 00:26:04,312
- [grunting]
- [clatters]

550
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:08,942
- [grunting]
- [thuds]

551
00:26:11,403 --> 00:26:14,406
[intense music playing]

552
